caption: I usually order their quesadillas and they are very good. So today I decided to try out their Birria, and oh my gosh it had so much oil that I could not eat it. Food is amazing 🤩 I love their Grande barbacoa burrito ! ! ! First Time Eating From There. I ordered from door dash Food was still warm and they give you a great amount of food I think it very much worth the price. Even the sour cream and guacamole comes in a great size.  Usually people give you a little bit. But, they give you more than enough. Oh ! ! ! And their pickled red onions are soooo tasty. I love the freshness of the red onions and the balance between the salt and vinegar. I can eat it alone ! !  I definitely would eat there again. The conversation that the employees had while customers waited was beyond me...the so called manager COMPLAINED about the work day for Cinco de mayo...stating how busy it was and how a woman called to check on her delivery saying the delivery was taking too long and how her children were hungry....the manager stated that its not his fault that her children were hungry and that SHE WAS A BAD MOTHER FOR ALLOWING HER CHILDREN TO GET HUNGRY...that was strike number 1..So my food is prepared and I realize the taco was a soft shell...I asked if they had hard shells because I don't like the soft bread. The response was no. I asked to change order and apologized for the inconvenience...mind you the menu doesn't state anything about the tacos being hard shell or soft. The male cashier said to me "well your food is already prepared" sucks his teeth and walks out...now this is strike 2. So the manager the same one who mentioned the female caller was A BAD MOTHER...was actually nicer than the cashier with the hoop nose ring. He was willing to change order but stated that "REAL" tacos are ALWAYS SOFT...AND THAT AMERICANS ARE THE ONES THAT STARTED THE HARD TACO TREND...strike 3...I just took the food and left I couldn't take it anymore. If I can give them a quarter of a star I would!
